Quote.create(:quote=>"Networks come to a grinding halt when too many collisions occur. Ethernet bridges resolve this problem by physically breaking an Ethernet into two or more segments. This arrangement means that devices communicating on one side of the bridge do not collide with devices communicating on the other side of the bridge. Bridges also learn which devices are on each side and only transfer traffic to the network containing the destination device.", :score=> 0, :category_id=>43, :matchups => 0)
