Quote.create(:quote=>"Asynchronous Transfer Mode (ATM) is one of the primary Layer 2 WAN transport protocols. Originally developed as high-speed public WAN transport for voice, video, and data, ATM was later modified by the ATM Forum to include transport over private networks. Although LAN implementations of ATM have never been popular (because of the explosion of Ethernet's popularity), use of ATM on WANs is widespread.", :score=> 0, :category_id=>43, :matchups => 0)
