Quote.create(:quote=>"Power cannot accrue to those who squander their treasure of words.", :score=> 0, :category_id=>49, :matchups => 0)
Quote.create(:quote=>"Louis XIV was a man of very few words.", :score=> 0, :category_id=>49, :matchups => 0)
Quote.create(:quote=>"His infamous \"I shall see\" was one of several extremely short phrases that he would apply to all manner of requests.", :score=> 0, :category_id=>49, :matchups => 0)
Quote.create(:quote=>"Louis was not always this way; as a young man he was known for talking at length, delighting in his own eloquence. His later taciturnity was self-imposed, an act, a mask he used to keep everybody below him off-balance. No one knew exactly where he stood, or could predict his reactions. No one could try to deceive him by saying what they thought he wanted to hear, because no one knew what he wanted to hear. As they talked on and on to the silent Louis, they revealed more and more about themselves, information he would later use against them to great effect.", :score=> 0, :category_id=>49, :matchups => 0)
Quote.create(:quote=>"Power is in many ways a game of appearances, and when you say less than necessary, you inevitably appear greater and more powerful than you are. Your silence will make other people uncomfortable. Humans are machines of interpretation and explanation; they have to know what you are thinking. When you carefully control what you reveal, they cannot pierce your intentions or your meaning.", :score=> 0, :category_id=>49, :matchups => 0)
